name: AutoGen
description: AutoGen is a framework that enables the development of LLM applications using multiple agents that can converse with each other to solve tasks.

name: Stable Diffusion
description: Stable Diffusion by Stability AI is a state of the art text-to-image model that generates images from text. opensource

name: gptcomet
description: CLI tool to help you generate commit message and review changes. Support mutiple providers and languages.

name: poorcoder
description: A collection of Bash scripts to extract code context, apply changes from markdown, and generate AI commit messages while using web-based LLMs.

name: Vibe Compiler (vibec)
description: A self-compiling tool that transforms markdown-based prompt stacks into code and tests using LLM generation. Works with any LLM via OpenRouter, including Claude, ChatGPT, and Grok.

name: AutoComplete.sh
description: CLI tool that adds AI-powered command-line suggestions directly to your terminal with just type to return the top suggestions for you.

name: code-collator
description: CLI tool that creates a single markdown file that describes your entire codebase to language models. Useful for AI-coding assistance from the ClaudeChatGPT web interface rather than via the API.

name: GPT Migrate
description: CLI agent that converts a full-stack application from one language or framework to another. Uses GPT-4 32k context.

name: Bolt.diy
description: Open source version of Bolt.new that supports multiple LLM providers including Groq, Anthropic, Ollama, OpenRouter, Gemini, LMStudio, Mistral, xAI, HuggingFace, DeepSeek

name: MutahunterAI
description: Accelerate developer productivity and code security by finding vulnerabilities in code and generating tests for them. Open Source and available as a CLI or CICD pipeline.
